        "reverse_layout": false,
        "caption": "",
        "body_text": "<p>or decades, homeowners have been sold a myth: that security requires \"blinding brightness.\" The standard solution has been the motion-activated dual floodlight—a fixture that blasts 2,000+ lumens into a dark yard the moment a leaf blows. We call this <em>The Glare Paradox</em>.</p>",
        "body_text_2": "<p>When a high-intensity light suddenly activates in the dark, your pupils instantly constrict. This biological reflex effectively \"blinds\" you to anything outside that specific cone of light. By creating a pool of hyper-bright light, you inadvertently create \"black holes\" of shadow immediately surrounding it.</p><p>True visibility requires low-contrast adaptation. You want your pupils to remain dilated so they can scan the entire perimeter. This is only possible with soft, continuous illumination rather than sudden bursts of intensity.</p>",
